elements.description:
Element that renders a calendar cell for a given date (and for non-date cells in the calendar).

### Usage

    <px-calendar-cell
      display-date="{{...}}"
      first-range-date="{{...}}"
      second-range-date="{{...}}">
    </px-calendar-cell>

properties.name: blockFutureDates
properties.description: Set this attribute when you do not want to allow future dates to be selected (future dates will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: blockPastDates
properties.description: Set this attribute when you do not want to allow past dates to be selected (past dates will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: min
properties.description: The minimum / earliest allowed date, as an ISO 8601 String or a Moment object (dates before this will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: max
properties.description: The maximum / latest allowed date, as an ISO 8601 String or a Moment object (dates after this will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: fromMoment
properties.description: Moment object start date & time

properties.name: toMoment
properties.description: Moment object end date & time

properties.name: displayDate
properties.description: Moment object with date to display in this cell

properties.name: displayMode
properties.description:
What the calendar should display:
 'day': day number
 'month': month
 'year': year

properties.name: blockDatesAfter
properties.description: blocks the selection/navigation for any dates after this one.

properties.name: blockDatesBefore
properties.description: blocks the selection/navigation for any dates before this one.

methods.name: _updateDate
methods.description: Go through each cell and decide if it has a day in that month, is it selected, inbetween selected, etc.

elements.description: All datetime components rely on Moment.js and Moment Timezone. This element renders a calendar for a given decade, year, or month, based on `display-mode` and `base-date`. A user can either select a range of dates or a single date, based on the `prevent-range-selection` property. User-selected values can be read out from the `range` or `single-selected-date` properties accordingly. A single date or range can be pre-set by manually setting either `from-moment` (single date) or `from-moment` and `to-moment` (range) using valid Moment.js objects. ### Usage ### Styling The following custom properties are available for styling: Custom property | Description :----------------|:------------- `--px-calendar-text-color` | Default text color for dates on the calendar `--px-calendar-text-color--hover` | Text color for dates when hovered `--px-calendar-text-color--selected` | Text color for dates when selected `--px-calendar-title-color` | Color for the title and arrows `--px-calendar-sub-labels--text-color` | Text color for days of the week `--px-calendar-today-border` | Border color for today's date `--px-calendar-background-color--hover` | Background color for dates when hovered `--px-calendar-background-color--pressed` | Background color for dates when pressed `--px-calendar-background-color--selected` | Background color for dates when selected `--px-calendar-alt-background-color` | Background color for the range between start and end dates

properties.name: fromMoment
properties.description: Moment object start date & time

properties.name: toMoment
properties.description: Moment object end date & time

properties.name: presetRanges
range
properties.description:
(required: 'px-{datetime}-range-{picker}')

This is the object you use to instantiate px-datetime components. You can retrieve the object through 2-way data-binding.

Formated as ISO8601 strings
```
{
   "from": "2013-01-07T22:44:30.652Z",
   "to" : "2013-02-04T22:44:30.652Z"
}
```

This object which will be changed when the user Submits their new selected range.

properties.name: baseDate
properties.description: Moment object used as the base for the calendar (to decide which month to display)

properties.name: displayMode
properties.description:
What the calendar should display:
 - 'day': calendar displays all days of a month
 - 'month': calendar displays all months in a year
 - 'year': calendar displays a 10 years range

properties.name: _currentDisplayMode
properties.description:
What the calendar should display:
 - 'day': calendar displays all days of a month
 - 'month': calendar displays all months in a year
 - 'year': calendar displays a 10 year range

 Can internally change when the user clicks the title and changes the mode

properties.name: preventRangeSelection
properties.description:
(optional)

By default, the calendar will allow the user to select a date range by clicking on two
different dates. If this property is set, the user will only be able to select a single date
each time she clicks.

If this property is set, then the 'singleSelectedDate' property will reflect the selected date. Otherwise
the 'range' property should be observed and will reflect the selected date range.

properties.name: singleSelectedDate
properties.description:
(optional)

Reflects the selected date in ISO8601 string if the calendar is preventing range selection.
Otherwise the 'range' property should be observed.

properties.name: hidePreviousButton
properties.description:
(optional)

Hides the 'previous' button on the calendar.

properties.name: hideNextButton
properties.description:
(optional)

Hides the 'next' button on the calendar.

properties.name: shrink
properties.description:
(optional)

If set, allows the calendar picker to shrink rather than have a constant size.
Typically the height would shrink when choosing months or years

properties.name: isAtSelectionLevel
properties.description:
Whether the calendar picker is currently at the selection level: showing days
in day mode, choosing month in month mode or showing years in year mode.

properties.name: _valuesDisplayed
properties.description: The values currently displayed in the calendar cells, days, months or years

methods.name: _setMomentFromRange
methods.description:
Converts range into from and to moments

Triggered from a click on cancel, submit, esc, or enter

methods.name: _setRangeFromMoment
methods.description:
Converts 'toMoment' and 'fromMoment' to ISO8601 strings, then set the range with the strings.

Triggered from a click on cancel, submit, esc, or enter

methods.name: _applyMomentToString
methods.description: Applies the current 'from' and 'to' moment objects to the external facing 'range' strings

methods.name: _rollbackMomentFromString
methods.description: Rollbacks the current 'from' and 'to' moment objects to the external facing 'range' strings

methods.name: _validateRangeOrder
methods.description: Validation for the range. Makes sure the ranges are in chronological order

return.desc: true if chronological order, false otherwise

methods.name: _notifyRangeChanged
methods.description:
This event is fired differently depending on config:
 - If the px-datetime component has an Apply button, then it is fired when the
  user clicks the Apply button (or presses enter) AND the selected date/time is valid
 - If the px-datetime component does not have an Apply button, then it is fired
  every time a change is made to the date/time AND the selected date/time is valid

methods.name: _onNextDisplayMode
methods.description: Change the display mode after the user clicked the title
